message.content: This command establishes an SSH connection to a remote server named `ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com` using the private key file `UserKey.pem` located in the user's home directory (`~/`) as the authentication method. The `-C` option enables compression to improve transfer speed, and the `-L` option creates a local forwarding of port 25900 on the local machine to port 5900 on the remote server using the `localhost` address. This allows you to access the remote server's X11 display over SSH from your local machine by specifying `localhost:25900` as the DISPLAY variable in any application that uses X11.
